==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Trade-off
<hw>Trade"-off</hw></mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>the exchange of one thing (object, right,
opportunity) for another of approximately equal value, so as to seal a
bargain, or effect a compromise.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>the giving up of one desired objective in order to
attain another, when both cannot be achieved at the same time; <as>as,
the factory workers viewed the <ex>trade-off</ex> of air quality for
jobs as a necessary evil</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trader</ent>⟦br⟧
